{{Development | tools}}This article explains how to install and configure command line tools for use with [[ImageJ]] development.

== Install and configure command line tools ==

=== Setting up command line tools on Windows ===
Install [[Git]], [[Maven]], and Java SE using [https://chocolatey.org/ Chocolatey]:
<source lang="bash">
choco install -y git maven jdk8
</source>
We also heartily recommend installing [https://www.cygwin.com/ Cygwin]:
<source lang="bash">
choco install -y cyg-get
</source>

=== Setting up command line tools on Mac OS X ===
Install [[Git]] and [[Maven]] using [http://brew.sh/ Homebrew]:
<source lang="bash">
brew install git maven bash-completion
</source>
Download and install [http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/ Java SE] from Oracle.

=== Setting up command line tools on Ubuntu ===
<source lang="bash">
sudo apt-get install default-jdk git maven
</source>

== Download the source ==
<source lang="bash">
git clone git://github.com/imagej/imagej
</source>
See the [[Source Code]] page for further details.

== Build the source ==
<source lang="bash">
cd imagej
mvn
</source>

== Launch the program ==
<source lang="bash">
mvn -Pexec
</source>

=== Launching alternative user interfaces ===
<source lang="bash">
mvn -Dimagej.ui=swing -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=swing-mdi -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=awt -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=pivot -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=swt -Pexec
</source>

